    narr:narration """This hub archives the verbatim record of the aswritten narrative, tracing its evolution from early 2025 through mid-2026. The trajectory begins with [early product-demonstration moments](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletIncredibleQuote) and [modular-synthesizer metaphors](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletModularSynthesizerQuote) that framed the AI as a guide rather than a prescriber. By April 2026, the focus shifted to the [buyer-side thesis](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerCTOInformationCommodity), where the customer’s CTO identified [AI slop](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerCTOAISlopQuote) as the primary problem. May 2026 solidified the [curated-memory principle](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerArchitectNotComfortableQuote), with both the CTO and chief architect aligning on [human-review requirements](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletCantAutomateQuote) and [PR-with-unit-tests metaphors](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_CustomerCTOPRMetaphorQuote). The narrative reached a [base-camp milestone](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_BaseCampQuote) in May, before moving toward July 2026, where Scarlet refined the [narrative architecture method](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletNarrativeArchitectureMethodQuote) and [constellation framing](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletQuote_Constellation). Throughout, the governing style remains [direct block-quoted speech](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_DirectQuoteStyle) as the primary evidence, distinguishing between [demo-share and product-goal](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_ScarletDemoVsProductQuote).""" ;
